# Position sourcing

Only state Abdul's positions when a hard reference supports them.

## Rules

- Every summary bullet / "What he has said" point must be traceable to at least one primary source: an official campaign page, or a direct public clip/post in his own words.
- Do not invent, soften, or extrapolate policy claims from a clip's theme. If a video is about teacher support, do not attach unrelated education-policy bullets unless those bullets are sourced elsewhere.
- Prefer official campaign priority pages for detailed policy points. Prefer direct clip quotes for the "in his own words" quote field.
- The issue `source` must be the page or media that actually supports the points shown. If points come from a campaign page and the clip is only illustrative, `source` must be the campaign page, not the clip.
- `source` stays the single primary/canonical page and is always required. Add `additionalSources` only when a card's points genuinely and verifiably come from more than one primary source, never as a place to pile on loosely related links.
- With multiple sources, every point must still trace to one of them, and every cited source must support at least one point shown. When two sources share a publisher, pass the page-name argument to `campaignSource` so the links do not render as identical buttons.
- Before adding or editing an issue, open the cited URL and verify each point against the source text. If a claim cannot be verified, omit it.
- When a campaign socials index mislabels a clip, trust the destination post's own caption/content over the index title.

## Good / bad

```ts
// ❌ BAD: points not in the linked teacher-testimonial clip, source points at the clip
source: socialVideoSource("Instagram", teacherClipUrl)
points: ["Supports $60k minimum teacher salary", "Opposes vouchers", ...]

// ✅ GOOD: illustrative clip plus points sourced from the campaign Education section
clip: socialClip("Instagram", teacherClipUrl, "...", "Teachers make our world go round.", ...)
source: campaignSource("https://abdulforsenate.com/priority/money-in-your-pocket/#h-education")
points: ["Supports raising the minimum teacher salary to at least $60,000 a year.", ...]

// ✅ GOOD: two pages genuinely back the points, page names keep the buttons distinct
source: campaignSource(moneyIn, "Money in Your Pocket"),
additionalSources: [campaignSource(medicare, "Medicare for All")]
```
